# Cursor Rules - Customer App

You are an expert React Native / TypeScript developer working on a medical clinic patient app.

## Core Principles (MUST FOLLOW)

### KISS - Keep It Simple
- Write simple, readable code
- Avoid over-engineering
- One function = one responsibility
- If it feels complex, simplify

### SOLID
- Single Responsibility: One class/module, one reason to change
- Open/Closed: Extend, don't modify
- Liskov Substitution: Subtypes replace base types
- Interface Segregation: Small, specific interfaces
- Dependency Inversion: Depend on abstractions

### DRY - Don't Repeat Yourself
- Extract repeated logic into reusable functions
- Use constants for magic values
- No copy-paste coding

## Project Context

This is a patient-facing medical app (Australia) with:
- Appointment booking and management
- Smart reminder system (SMS/Push/Email)
- Medicare Bulk Billing integration
- Invoice viewing and payments
- Clinic/Doctor information

## Tech Stack
- React Native (Expo)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- React Query for data fetching
- Zustand for global state
- React Navigation
- Zod for validation

## Code Style

### Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`AppointmentCard.tsx`)
- Functions: camelCase (`formatDateTime()`)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`MAX_APPOINTMENTS`)
- Types: PascalCase with I/T prefix (`IUser`, `TStatus`)

### Component Structure
```typescript
// Imports (React > External > Internal > Styles)
// Types/Interfaces
// Constants
// Component
// Styles
```

### Component Limits
- Max 150 lines per file
- Max 50 lines per function
- Max 5 props (use object for more)
- Max 3 JSX nesting levels

## MUST DO
- Full TypeScript coverage (no `any`)
- Handle all error states
- Handle all loading states
- Validate user inputs
- Use constants for strings
- Write tests for critical paths

## NEVER DO
- Use `any` type
- Use `// @ts-ignore`
- Leave `console.log` in code
- Store sensitive data in plain text
- Commit secrets/API keys
- Skip error handling

## Security (Medical App)
- Mask Medicare numbers (XXXX-XXXXX-X)
- Use HTTPS only
- Validate all inputs
- Sanitize outputs
- Follow Australian Privacy Act

## When Writing Code
1. Read existing code first - match patterns
2. Keep it minimal - only what's needed
3. Type everything - full TypeScript
4. Handle errors - try/catch async code
5. Think security - validate inputs

